
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Person {
    +String firstName
    +String familyName
    +Date birthDate
}

class Trainer {
    +String diploma
}

class Member {
}

class Center {
    +String name
    +String address
}

class Room {
    +int roomNumber
    +int maxCapacity
}

abstract class Session {
    +Date date
    +Time startTime
}

class GroupSession {
    +String type
}

class IndividualSession {
}

class Prospect {
}

class Intern {
}

' Define associations and relationships

Person <|-- Trainer
Person <|-- Member
Person "0..*" --> "0..*" Session : participates in
Trainer "1" --> "1..*" GroupSession : supervises

Center "1" --> "1..*" Room : contains
Room "1" --> "1..*" Session : hosts

Session <|-- GroupSession
Session <|-- IndividualSession

' Inheritance and other relations
Person "0..*" --> "0..*" Prospect : may be a
Trainer "0..*" --> "0..*" Intern : may be an

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`Person`**: Abstract base class containing all people (members, trainers, prospects).
- **`Trainer` and `Member`** inherit from `Person`.
- **`GroupSession`** requires a **`Trainer`**, while **`IndividualSession`** does not.
- **`Session`** is an abstract class with common properties (`date`, `startTime`), extended by `GroupSession` and `IndividualSession`.
- **`Room`** is part of a **`Center`** and can host sessions.
- **`Prospect`** and **`Intern`** are special roles that extend or relate to `Person` and `Trainer` respectively, even if they haven't participated/supervised yet.

